2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new approach that combines self-supervised and supervised learning for denoising. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a meta-learning algorithm for quick adaptation of parameters to specific inputs. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper deals with deep learning techniques for denoising. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with image denoising, which is a common task in multimedia processing.
